WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:03.537
Last season onThe Riches.

00:03.604 --> 00:06.239
‐ Now, who buys a house
on the Internet?
‐ A rich man.

00:06.306 --> 00:08.274
What about his job?
What about it?

00:08.341 --> 00:11.512
Someone's gonna come looking for
him. You tell me no one's coming
through them doors tomorrow?

00:11.578 --> 00:13.680
I don't know
who's coming through
those doors tomorrow.

00:13.747 --> 00:16.449
<i>Okay, I'm confused.</i>
<i>I don't get it.</i>
<i>What's the angle here?</i>

00:16.517 --> 00:18.184
How are we bleedin' 'em?
We're not bleeding
anyone.

00:18.251 --> 00:21.688
‐ Oh, we're not?
‐ Then what are we
doing here, Dad?

00:21.755 --> 00:23.657
The American dream.

00:23.724 --> 00:25.859
[ Cael ]
What?

00:25.926 --> 00:27.728
We're gonna steal it.

00:29.329 --> 00:32.165
Hi. I'm Doug. I'm Doug.
[ Deeper Voice ]
I'm Doug.

00:32.232 --> 00:35.869
Hi. Doug. Doug Rich.
[ Softer Voice ]
Doug Rich.

00:35.936 --> 00:37.638
Doug Rich,
meet your new team.

00:37.704 --> 00:41.742
Panco team, meet
your new legal chief.

00:41.808 --> 00:45.378
Doug!
[ Wayne's Voice ] Come and meet
our new neighbors.

00:45.445 --> 00:48.348
‐ I'm Jim.
This is my wife, Nina.
‐ <i>[ Nina ] Hi.</i>

00:48.414 --> 00:50.250
Andrea said we should
introduce ourselves.

00:50.316 --> 00:51.151
Wayne.
Dahlia.

00:51.217 --> 00:52.152
Doug.
Cherien.

00:52.218 --> 00:54.788
How do you do?
I'm Mrs. Doug Rich.

00:54.855 --> 00:58.692
Haven't you read
Calder v. Bull?
Yeah.

00:58.759 --> 01:03.964
Yeah. Have you read
Hester v. Straplink?
Ratzen v. Katzen?

01:04.030 --> 01:07.668
You are the best
goddamn lawyer I ever met.

01:07.734 --> 01:10.971
Dad, we have to do something.
Dale came here for us.
He's not going anywhere.

01:11.037 --> 01:13.640
[ Wayne ]
Dale seems to have been here
for a while now.

01:13.707 --> 01:16.677
He could've blown our cover
at any point and he didn't.
Why is that?

01:16.743 --> 01:19.112
He's Dale.
He's working an angle.
I don't know.

01:19.179 --> 01:21.447
‐ Doug.
‐ Dale.

01:21.515 --> 01:23.517
We have a lot to talk about,
my friend.

01:23.584 --> 01:26.720
Doug is a Republican.
His best friend is Pete.

01:26.787 --> 01:29.523
Pete's a mortgage broker
from Dallas. He's e‐mailed
twice about a golf trip.

01:29.590 --> 01:32.893
‐ Hello.
‐ Hi. Uh, is, uh, Doug here?

01:32.959 --> 01:34.695
Doug who?

01:34.761 --> 01:39.365
‐Pete?
‐Guess you're probably surprised
to see me here, Wayne.

01:39.432 --> 01:42.102
You and I both know
you're not Doug Rich,

01:42.168 --> 01:46.272
though everyone here
seems to think you are.

01:46.339 --> 01:51.277
<i>Who are you?</i>
<i>And where the hell is</i>
<i>my best friend, Doug Rich?</i>

01:55.381 --> 01:58.118
I don't like Wild Berry.
Oh.

01:58.184 --> 02:00.153
Yeah, you do.
You do.
I do? Oh.

02:00.220 --> 02:02.789
You like it. Okay.
[ Gurgles ]

02:02.856 --> 02:05.158
Okay.
Got about an hour.

02:05.225 --> 02:08.127
<i>[ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i>

02:08.193 --> 02:11.231
It's Hugh.
We don't have time
for Hugh.

02:11.297 --> 02:14.501
Hey. Hey, man.
Can we talk?

02:14.568 --> 02:16.703
What? It‐‐ Hugh, it is
4:00 in the morning.

02:16.770 --> 02:19.773
‐ She locked the doors on me.
‐ Wayne, we gotta go.

02:19.840 --> 02:23.710
And we had this fight.
I said some stuff.
I called her names.

02:23.777 --> 02:26.680
Pete is not dead.
He is asleep.
We do not have all day.

02:26.747 --> 02:29.716
Said I was the saddest person
she ever met.

02:29.783 --> 02:33.419
She didn't mean that.
She was upset.
We are headin' out.

02:33.486 --> 02:37.190
I'm here sittin' here,
telling you I need you.
[ Crying ]

02:37.257 --> 02:39.660
I'm on my way.

02:39.726 --> 02:41.628
[ Beeps ]

02:53.239 --> 02:56.643
<i>Oh, dear Lord.</i>
<i>What happened to you?</i>

02:58.011 --> 03:01.682
‐ I won't ask.
‐ Oh, Nina.

03:04.284 --> 03:06.319
I won't tell.
I know.

03:06.386 --> 03:08.454
I just wish‐‐

03:08.522 --> 03:10.456
Wish I could come
with you.

03:10.524 --> 03:12.726
I just wish
I had the guts.

03:12.793 --> 03:14.728
Mr. Rich?

03:16.162 --> 03:19.032
Mrs. Rich?
Everything okay up there?

03:19.099 --> 03:20.934
[ Pete ]
Please, help me!

03:22.002 --> 03:25.271
[ Panting ]

03:26.907 --> 03:28.809
You're...

03:30.343 --> 03:32.278
that guy in the truck.

03:32.345 --> 03:34.748
Yeah.
I'm a handyman.

03:34.815 --> 03:37.350
‐ Where we gonna go? Mexico?
‐ I vote Canada.

03:37.417 --> 03:39.485
‐ It's too far, Di. Come on.
‐ What do you say, baby?

03:39.553 --> 03:41.522
Wherever we go,
we gotta go right now.

03:41.588 --> 03:45.559
Mexico it is. Sorry, Di Di.
I could do with a margarita.

03:47.460 --> 03:49.996
[ Engine Cranks ]

03:52.265 --> 03:56.102
So this, uh,
Doug and Cherien‐‐

03:56.169 --> 03:58.839
the Riches?

03:58.905 --> 04:03.009
You known 'em for years?
They're real?

04:03.076 --> 04:05.045
Or they were.
[ Inhales ]

04:05.111 --> 04:10.517
And these people,
whoever they are‐‐
they took over their lives.

04:12.118 --> 04:15.021
Information like that
you could really hold
over somebody's head.

04:16.790 --> 04:19.125
You could use that
to get some serious green.

04:19.192 --> 04:22.262
You mean blackmail them?
Mmm.

04:22.328 --> 04:26.299
Are you out of your mind?
I don't want money.
I‐‐ I want my friends!

04:26.366 --> 04:30.103
I gotta go to the police,
have those two arrested.

04:30.170 --> 04:33.006
I have to find out
what they've done
with my friends.

04:33.073 --> 04:36.309
My God! What‐‐
What am I doing here?
What's wrong with me?

04:36.376 --> 04:40.413
They're getting away
as we speak.
No, they're not going anywhere.

04:40.480 --> 04:43.550
‐ Distributor cap's gone.
‐ Shit!

04:43.617 --> 04:45.719
Great. What the hell
are we gonna do, you guys?

04:45.786 --> 04:48.154
‐ It's gotta be Dale.
‐ That guy's probably
awake by now.

04:48.221 --> 04:50.023
No, no, no, no.
It's okay. It's okay.

04:50.090 --> 04:53.493
It's okay, 'cause, um‐‐
'cause your dad
has a plan.

04:54.160 --> 04:57.030
You comin'?

04:57.097 --> 05:00.233
[ Grunts ]

05:00.300 --> 05:02.936
[ Groans ]
Oh, God.

05:04.705 --> 05:07.073
Yeah, Pete.
I'm comin'.

05:08.241 --> 05:10.577
Let's go
for a little stroll.

05:13.680 --> 05:16.016
‐ You don't have a plan.
‐ Um‐‐

05:21.454 --> 05:23.657
‐ Well, not at the moment.
‐ Ah, shit.

05:23.724 --> 05:26.192
‐Shit.
‐We gotta get outta here.
Come on. How much money we got?

05:26.259 --> 05:29.863
‐ [ Cael ] Seven grand.
‐ Seven grand? Your dad fakes it
as a lawyer for three months,

05:29.930 --> 05:32.332
‐ and all we got
to show for it is seven grand?
‐ Calm down.

05:32.398 --> 05:35.068
‐ There's nowhere to run to.
‐ We gotta get outta here.
If Pete wakes up,

05:35.135 --> 05:37.504
calls the cops,
we're gonna get busted
for killing the Riches.

05:37.571 --> 05:41.307
Okay, this is what we'll do.
I'll go back to the house, get
the Mercedes, pick everyone up.

05:41.374 --> 05:43.777
No. The house could be
crawling with cops.
I'll take that risk.

05:43.844 --> 05:46.613
Wayne, Dale could be waitin'
for you anywhere.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.782
‐ Yeah, well,
I'll take that risk.
‐ Shit, Sam's gone.

05:51.251 --> 05:53.219
Sammi?
Sam.

05:53.286 --> 05:55.021
Sammi.
Sam?

05:55.088 --> 05:58.424
Sam? Sam?
Oh, Sam. Sam!

05:58.491 --> 06:00.994
‐ Wait, wait, wait!
‐ Baby,
what the hell?

06:01.061 --> 06:04.798
I have a plan.
Okay. Well, what's
your plan, sweetheart?

06:07.768 --> 06:10.003
Where'd you get this?
In the woods,
where you buried it.

06:10.070 --> 06:13.540
‐ I wanna give it to Pete.
‐ Gonna bribe Pete?

06:14.708 --> 06:16.610
You had this all along
without telling us?

06:16.677 --> 06:18.444
I was saving it
for a rainy day.

06:18.512 --> 06:20.480
Oh, my God.

06:20.547 --> 06:23.316
When Uncle Earl died
and your dad had to break
into Hugh's office...

06:23.383 --> 06:26.653
so that Dale wouldn't
kill him, that wasn't
rainy enough for you?

06:26.720 --> 06:29.389
‐ Not as rainy as this.
‐ You're gonna bribe Pete?

06:29.455 --> 06:33.193
No, you can't bribe Pete,
sweetheart. You can't bribe
men like Pete.

06:33.259 --> 06:35.261
Not with this.
Why not with this?

06:35.328 --> 06:39.600
Money makes the world go round.
Every man has his price.

06:39.666 --> 06:41.602
Hey.

06:43.103 --> 06:46.573
Okay, good try.
Go wait for us in the R. V.

06:46.640 --> 06:49.843
<i>[ Sniffles ]</i>

07:11.698 --> 07:14.434
All right.
Get in the car.

07:20.607 --> 07:22.976
What's wrong?
Get in the car.

07:24.811 --> 07:27.313
Want you to grab the kids,
get the hell outta here.

07:27.380 --> 07:30.517
I will meet you in Galveston.
Wayne, get in
the goddamn car.

07:30.584 --> 07:32.686
I'm not going, baby.

07:32.753 --> 07:35.956
Got the 40 grand
and the seven grand
we saved up.

07:36.022 --> 07:38.191
I'm gonna talk
to him.
Wayne.

07:38.258 --> 07:40.894
Like Sammi said,
"Money makes the world
go round."

07:40.961 --> 07:44.598
Wayne, he's a little boy.
You're a grown man.

07:44.665 --> 07:47.768
There's things you want,
and there's things that are.

07:47.834 --> 07:50.804
You gotta know
the difference.
I have to try.

07:50.871 --> 07:55.642
Baby, you can't bribe Pete.

07:55.709 --> 07:58.044
Don't you get it?
He's honest.

07:58.111 --> 08:02.182
Baby, then I will buy you
a little time and get
you closer to Mexico.

08:02.248 --> 08:04.050
Wayne, get in the goddamn car.

08:04.117 --> 08:07.387
If anyone's going to prison,
this time it's me.

08:07.453 --> 08:09.556
No, Wayne.

08:10.924 --> 08:12.859
Baby.

08:13.927 --> 08:16.196
[ Sighs ]

08:25.672 --> 08:28.575
[ Engine Starts ]

08:32.145 --> 08:34.847
[ Car Departs ]

08:34.914 --> 08:37.583
♪♪♪♪ [ Cartoon On TV ]

08:47.127 --> 08:49.429
[ Chattering On TV ]

08:49.495 --> 08:51.632
Pete?

08:52.999 --> 08:56.369
Pete!
[ Child's Voice On TV ]
Yes, I can!

08:56.436 --> 08:58.905
Pete!
Yes, I can!

08:58.972 --> 09:02.776
Where are you, Pete?
Hey, wait a minute!

09:02.843 --> 09:05.345
Now, you just go on.
You show 'em what
you're made of.

09:05.411 --> 09:07.514
[ Grunting ]
Like this.

09:07.581 --> 09:10.684
Pete?
<i>And plié</i>
<i>and arabesque.</i>

09:10.751 --> 09:13.353
[ Laughs ]
There you go.
Pete, you okay?

09:13.419 --> 09:18.559
There you go, Robin Hoodwinked.
I'll save you,
Maid Mary Jane!

09:19.693 --> 09:23.530
<i>I'll save you!</i>
<i>I'm coming!</i>

09:23.597 --> 09:26.332
Oh! Oh!
Pete?

09:26.399 --> 09:28.635
Boo!
[ Laughing ]
Jesus!

09:28.702 --> 09:32.238
I scared you.
[ Laughing ]

09:32.305 --> 09:35.175
‐ Ooh. Rough night, huh?
‐ Go shit yourself.

09:35.241 --> 09:39.112
Pete? Pete? Pete?
Pete, you okay?
[ Chuckles ]

09:39.179 --> 09:40.947
Where is he?
Shh!

09:41.014 --> 09:43.083
[ Dale ]
I love this part.

09:43.149 --> 09:45.719
<i>Oh.</i>

09:45.786 --> 09:48.589
[ Dale ]
Mmm! I spilled
a little bit on your bed.

09:48.655 --> 09:50.490
Pete?
Really nice bed.
It's very soft.

09:50.557 --> 09:52.258
Pete!
Pillowy.

09:52.325 --> 09:54.227
Pete!
Where are you, Pete?

09:55.395 --> 09:59.566
Mmm.
[ Line Ringing ]

09:59.633 --> 10:02.769
What did you do
with Pete?
Mmm.

10:04.771 --> 10:08.509
[ Woman's Voice ]
The mailbox for the subscriber
you are trying to reach is full.

10:08.575 --> 10:10.511
‐ Pete who?
‐ <i>Please try again later.</i>

10:10.577 --> 10:12.646
Pete!
I'm just pulling your leg.

10:12.713 --> 10:17.183
You're talking about
your buddy, right?
Talking about your buddy Pete?

10:17.250 --> 10:19.419
Where are you, Pete?
Pete!
You really got‐‐

10:19.485 --> 10:22.155
You're really gonna wanna‐‐
You're really gonna wanna
see this one.

10:22.222 --> 10:24.558
Yes, sirree.

10:24.625 --> 10:28.394
<i>Is that, uh, you, Doug?</i>

10:28.461 --> 10:32.899
‐ Please try your call
again later.
‐ That you and your other wife?

10:38.605 --> 10:42.142
What do you want?
What do I want?

10:42.208 --> 10:46.346
[ Sighs ]
I wanna sit down
and formulate a little plan.

10:49.249 --> 10:52.118
Blow it out your ass.
So what'd you do?
Did you kill 'em, Wayne?

10:52.185 --> 10:54.955
Pete!
Kill 'em, move into their house,
start living their lives?

10:55.021 --> 10:57.457
Pete!
Is that what you did?
You stole their names?

10:57.524 --> 11:00.026
I didn't kill anyone.
No. Where's Doug
and Cherien Rich, huh?

11:00.093 --> 11:03.263
Where the hell are
Doug and Cherien Rich?

11:15.809 --> 11:20.480
I got all the cards, Wayne.
I'm holding all the cards,
and you're holding none.

11:20.547 --> 11:24.050
So, what do you wanna do?

11:24.785 --> 11:27.954
[ Groaning, Coughing ]

11:30.123 --> 11:33.259
‐ Where is he?
‐ Screw you.

11:33.326 --> 11:36.229
<i>It's just a little blood.</i>
<i>Calm down. Oh.</i>

11:37.397 --> 11:40.033
‐ Right now. Where is he?
‐ Put that thing away.

11:40.100 --> 11:42.402
‐ Where is he?
‐ Look, Pete's alive.

11:42.468 --> 11:45.271
<i>He's just a little hurt,</i>
<i>but he's fine.</i>

11:45.338 --> 11:47.340
‐ Bullshit!
‐ Look, he was gonna go
to the cops.

11:47.407 --> 11:50.877
<i>I had to stop him.</i>
<i>I did you a favor.</i>

11:56.249 --> 11:58.251
I did you a favor!

11:58.318 --> 12:01.054
Wayne, wait. I did you
a goddamn favor, Wayne!

12:02.255 --> 12:04.791
<i>Where are you go‐‐</i>
<i>I did you a favor!</i>

12:06.492 --> 12:09.329
What are you doing?
None of your damn business!

12:09.395 --> 12:12.032
Do you think I'm stupid?
Do you think I'm a moron?

12:12.098 --> 12:14.167
‐ Well‐‐
‐ Look, you ain't
gonna find him.

12:14.234 --> 12:17.303
He is safe and sound,
tucked away.

12:17.370 --> 12:20.473
Yeah?
[ Line Ringing ]

12:20.541 --> 12:23.409
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

12:23.476 --> 12:27.948
[ Woman's Voice ]
The mailbox of the subscriber
you are trying to reach is full.

12:48.201 --> 12:50.103
Shit.

13:06.887 --> 13:10.156
Hey, man.
Man, wake up.

13:14.360 --> 13:16.963
[ Hammer Hits Ground ]
Come on. Come on.
Wake up! Wake up!

13:20.233 --> 13:23.637
I j‐‐ Uh, I just, um‐‐
You‐‐ You killed him.

13:23.704 --> 13:27.674
I just‐‐ I hit him, and then‐‐
But he fought back. He‐‐

13:27.741 --> 13:30.544
‐ You murdered him!
‐ No, I did‐‐
I did you a favor.

13:30.611 --> 13:34.681
‐ You murdered him!
‐ I did‐‐ You were
in a shit storm,

13:34.748 --> 13:38.619
and‐and‐and I swept up
all the shit.
Back up, Dale.

13:38.685 --> 13:41.622
‐ You owe me big goddamn
favors, Doug Rich!
‐ Oh, yeah?

13:41.688 --> 13:43.323
‐ You‐‐
‐ Just back up. Back up.

13:43.389 --> 13:45.792
‐ What are you doin'?
‐ I'm gettin' the hell away
from you!

13:45.859 --> 13:47.994
‐ Jesus.
‐ [ Engine Revs ]

13:49.195 --> 13:51.532
I will call the cops.
I will call the cops on you.

13:51.598 --> 13:53.634
‐ I don't care!
‐ Then they will think
that you did it,

13:53.700 --> 13:56.503
‐ because people saw
you with Pete.
‐ Well, call 'em! Go on!

13:56.570 --> 13:58.505
Call 'em!
[ Grunts ]
I will tell them‐‐

13:58.572 --> 14:00.674
I will tell them that
you killed the Riches.

14:00.741 --> 14:02.743
Just go ahead and do it,
goddamn it!

14:02.809 --> 14:04.978
‐ [ Tires Squealing ]
‐ [ Grunts ]

14:05.045 --> 14:08.749
‐ Whoa!
‐ [ Wayne ]
Oh, shit.

14:08.815 --> 14:10.951
[ Groans ]

14:14.487 --> 14:16.456
Jesus.

14:17.658 --> 14:19.593
[ Groaning ]
Hugh.

14:19.660 --> 14:22.028
Shit.

14:27.968 --> 14:30.236
Help me get him in the house.

14:31.805 --> 14:33.840
Come on.

14:33.907 --> 14:35.909
All right, Mama.
Mind your head.

14:35.976 --> 14:39.212
Get your foot in.
Here's your blanket.

14:39.279 --> 14:42.549
‐ Hey, hey, hey.
What are you doin'?
‐ It's my stuff.

14:42.616 --> 14:45.018
‐ Take that back.
‐ Oh, come on, Mom.
I actually bought this shit.

14:45.085 --> 14:48.622
Well, you should've robbed it,
'cause we're only taking
necessities. Go on, Di.

14:48.689 --> 14:51.592
You ask me, you never
should've let him go back.
I'm not asking you.

14:51.658 --> 14:54.394
‐ Yeah, Mom. It's bad luck.
‐ Don't say that!

14:54.460 --> 14:57.363
Mom, it's bad luck.
We work when we're together.
You know that.

14:57.430 --> 14:59.866
Well, we're not together, okay?
Your dad is a stubborn ass.

14:59.933 --> 15:02.669
We have to wait
for him, Mom.
We have to go back for him.

15:02.736 --> 15:06.272
<i>Don't you think I tried?</i>
<i>Hey, look. I know</i>
<i>you're scared.</i>

15:06.339 --> 15:08.742
This is what we do.
We can do this, all right?

15:08.809 --> 15:11.377
<i>We split apart.</i>
<i>We come back together.</i>
<i>We go on the road.</i>

15:11.444 --> 15:13.514
Um, just how we live
our lives.

15:15.081 --> 15:17.984
You forgotten that?

15:19.252 --> 15:21.555
Go on. Go close up
the R. V. Let's go.

15:24.257 --> 15:28.028
Oh. You can't take all
those books, sweetheart.

15:28.094 --> 15:30.363
‐ How many can I take?
‐ Well, none of them.

15:30.430 --> 15:33.433
I mean,
we're fully loaded up.

15:33.499 --> 15:35.936
Oh, Jesus Christ.

15:36.002 --> 15:38.038
We don't need these
damn buffer clothes anyhow.

15:38.104 --> 15:40.140
Go on. Don't tell
your brother or sister.

15:45.378 --> 15:48.982
[ Cael ]
Whoa. Easy there,
speedy. Man.

15:49.049 --> 15:53.319
Got to keep your eyes
on the road, Ma. Eyes on‐‐
Eyes on the road, Ma.

15:55.055 --> 15:56.957
Watch it!

15:57.023 --> 15:59.459
Oh! Shit. Sorry.

16:02.829 --> 16:04.598
[ Di Di ]
What the hell is that?

16:06.700 --> 16:08.334
[ Dahlia Exhales ]

16:08.401 --> 16:10.436
[ Di Di ]
Mom, what is that?

16:16.009 --> 16:18.745
[ Dahlia ]
Oh, shit. Nina?

16:24.150 --> 16:27.788
I changed my mind.
As it happens, I do have 'em.

16:27.854 --> 16:30.624
‐ Have what?
‐ The guts.

16:30.691 --> 16:34.728
Oh. Nina, sweetheart,
you can't come with us.

16:34.795 --> 16:36.963
My life's in shambles,
Dahlia.

16:37.030 --> 16:40.000
My future's bleak,
my marriage is bust.

16:40.066 --> 16:42.102
I mean, look at me.

16:42.168 --> 16:45.371
Do I look like a woman
with something to lose?

16:45.438 --> 16:47.574
I guess not.

16:47.641 --> 16:50.110
Mom, we can't.

16:50.176 --> 16:53.279
Cael, get in the back.
Come on.

16:57.751 --> 17:00.854
‐ Get in, Gypsy Rose Lee.
‐ Sorry, Grandma.

17:00.921 --> 17:05.290
Come on, Sammi.
You don't need all that space
for your little butt.

17:05.358 --> 17:07.627
[ Cael ]
Squish.
[ Di Di ] Sorry.

17:07.694 --> 17:10.496
[ Man ] And in local news,
the political scandal
continues to grow‐‐

17:10.564 --> 17:13.398
What's wrong with Justin?
...Ducaine Mayor
Justin Lemieux.

17:13.465 --> 17:15.401
Don't move. Just keep‐‐
Hugh?
Mmm.

17:15.468 --> 17:17.738
Keep this against
your head, okay?
Oh.

17:17.804 --> 17:20.473
Justin's busted.
...with an alleged
prostitute.

17:20.540 --> 17:24.144
‐ Who are you?
‐ I'm Doug Rich.

17:24.210 --> 17:27.714
‐ ...with the mayor continuing
to deny all charges.
‐ Your friend?

17:27.781 --> 17:31.918
‐ Then why'd you try to kill me?
‐ I didn't know
you were there, Hugh.

17:31.985 --> 17:34.921
‐ Bullshit.
‐ No, I was just back‐‐
I was coming to see you.

17:34.988 --> 17:38.024
That's really bullshit.
You never even asked
where I was‐‐

17:38.091 --> 17:40.527
Jesus! Who the hell
is that?
Whoa.

17:40.594 --> 17:44.130
‐ Hey there, Mr. Panetta.
‐ Doug, what the hell's
goin' on?

17:44.197 --> 17:46.066
Hugh,
this is Dale.
Ah.

17:46.132 --> 17:49.670
He is a local handyman.
He is just helping me
around the house.

17:49.736 --> 17:53.006
At 4:00 in the mornin'.
Well, we had a spillage.

17:53.073 --> 17:57.010
[ Beeping ]
[ Groaning ]

17:57.077 --> 17:59.245
Okay. Okay,
just stay here.

17:59.312 --> 18:02.215
[ Groans ]
Man!

18:02.282 --> 18:05.552
We have been acquainted,
Mr. Panetta, at your wedding.

18:05.619 --> 18:09.189
That's a sweet ride you have
out there‐‐ the Denali.

18:09.255 --> 18:13.326
‐ [ Hugh ] Yeah.
‐ Vortec 6.2 liter.

18:13.393 --> 18:16.863
I'm gonna have one of those
one day, if I work hard.

18:16.930 --> 18:19.933
‐ That's what I tell myself.
‐ Whatever floats your boat.

18:20.000 --> 18:22.936
[ Hugh Groans ]

18:23.003 --> 18:24.905
Help you out.
Whoa. Easy, easy.

18:24.971 --> 18:27.140
‐ What?
‐ Your hands.

18:27.207 --> 18:30.276
‐ What?
‐ Kinda dirty.

18:30.343 --> 18:35.315
‐ [ Chuckles ] So?
‐ So I don't like it. Germs.

18:35.381 --> 18:38.084
‐Little germs never hurt nobody.
‐No, I said don't touch me.
[ Stammering ]

18:38.151 --> 18:40.854
Gee! Gee!
Tell him not to touch me!

18:40.921 --> 18:45.125
‐ Shh!
‐ <i>No, get away.</i>
<i>Get away from me!</i>

18:46.727 --> 18:49.295
[ Hugh ]
Oh, man. No!

18:49.362 --> 18:52.899
‐ Morning, Officer.
‐ Is this your vehicle, sir?

18:52.966 --> 18:54.901
It is. I am so sorry.

18:54.968 --> 18:57.938
Well, you realize that it's,
uh, illegally parked up here
on your lawn.

18:58.004 --> 19:01.975
I know. I know. I needed
the bathroom so bad,
I just‐‐ Pssh.

19:02.042 --> 19:05.612
Well, I'm sorry to bother you
at this time of night, sir,
but we just can't have this.

19:05.679 --> 19:09.916
I‐‐ I understand.
This is no bother at all,
Officer... Delroy.

19:09.983 --> 19:13.587
"Del‐roy."
I'm, uh, the new cohead
of Edenfalls Security.

19:13.654 --> 19:16.890
Well, it is very good
to meet you,
Officer Delroy.

19:16.957 --> 19:18.892
I am Doug Rich.

19:18.959 --> 19:21.728
So you will repark the vehicle?
Absolutely. I will.
The key's inside.

19:21.795 --> 19:23.597
I'll just‐‐
When?

19:23.664 --> 19:26.833
It'll be done.
I will do it right away.

19:26.900 --> 19:29.670
[ Metal Creaking ]
[ Cael ]
Car sounds awful.

19:29.736 --> 19:32.673
[ Sighs ]
Mom, it's gettin' worse.
You gotta pull over.

19:32.739 --> 19:35.509
We can't stop.
Cops may have an A. P. B.
out on us.

19:35.576 --> 19:38.579
The car is bleeding
antifreeze, Ma.

19:38.645 --> 19:40.614
Okay, would you just
stay with me, please,
children?

19:40.681 --> 19:42.983
We're gonna pull
in the next town,
dump this piece of shit.

19:43.049 --> 19:46.152
Cael's gonna steal a new car,
'cause that's what he does,
and that's what we do.

19:46.219 --> 19:48.522
Mom, I really don't
want to go Mexico.

19:48.589 --> 19:51.491
You're gonna have to go to
Mexico, sweetheart, because
it's either that or prison.

19:51.558 --> 19:55.529
So, <i>adios, amigo.</i>
<i>La</i> freakin' <i>cucaracha.</i>

19:55.596 --> 19:58.364
So Doug is not a lawyer.

19:58.431 --> 20:00.466
He isn't even Doug.

20:00.534 --> 20:03.469
<i>His name's Wayne.</i>

20:03.537 --> 20:06.640
Wayne Malloy.
Wayne? Well‐‐

20:06.707 --> 20:09.342
And you're
Dahlia Malloy?
That's right.

20:09.409 --> 20:12.646
And the kids?
Kids are Malloys too.

20:15.015 --> 20:16.850
Then who are the Riches?

20:17.984 --> 20:19.920
[ Sniffles ]
I don't know.

20:19.986 --> 20:22.322
You mean you never
met 'em?

20:24.490 --> 20:28.094
We just stole their
credit cards, Nina. We're‐We're
not their best friends.

20:28.161 --> 20:32.465
‐ So you're con artists.
‐ That's right.

20:32.533 --> 20:35.401
Some kind of
identity thieves.
Ha.

20:35.468 --> 20:39.205
Yeah.
W‐We're drifters, Nina.

20:39.272 --> 20:42.876
We are grifters and drifters
and nomads.

20:42.943 --> 20:45.045
We are the scourge of
the goddamned earth.

20:45.111 --> 20:47.681
We are Travellers!
Right?

20:50.350 --> 20:53.587
Mmm, don't make Mama sing.

20:53.654 --> 20:57.457
<i>Come on.</i>
<i>♪♪ Busted flat</i>
<i>in Baton Rouge ♪♪</i>

20:57.524 --> 20:59.626
♪♪ Waitin' on a train ♪♪

20:59.693 --> 21:02.362
♪♪ Feelin' 'bout as faded
as my jeans ♪♪

21:02.428 --> 21:04.631
♪♪ Bobby flagged a diesel down ♪♪

21:04.698 --> 21:06.733
<i>♪♪ Fore the rain ♪♪</i>

21:06.800 --> 21:09.903
<i>♪♪ Drove it all the way</i>
<i>to New Orleans ♪♪</i>

21:09.970 --> 21:12.739
Would you please sing with me?
We're living large, man.
We're on the road.

21:12.806 --> 21:15.642
Come on, goddamn it. Sing.
♪♪ Freedom's just another word ♪♪

21:15.709 --> 21:18.545
♪♪ For nothin' left to lose ♪♪

21:18.612 --> 21:22.683
♪♪ Nothin', I said
nothin', honey
if it ain't free ♪♪

21:22.749 --> 21:26.152
♪♪ And feelin' good was
easy enough when ♪♪

21:26.219 --> 21:28.822
♪♪ Bobby sang the blues ♪♪

21:28.889 --> 21:31.692
♪♪ Feelin' good was
good enough for me ♪♪
<i>[ Engine Sputters ]</i>

21:31.758 --> 21:34.661
‐ Shit. Oh, my God.
‐ [ Cael ]
And there she goes.

21:34.728 --> 21:36.763
[ Di Di ]
You like that song?
Nice. That's good, Mom.

21:36.830 --> 21:38.999
Aw, shit.
[ Di Di ]
Thank goodness.

21:39.065 --> 21:40.901
I should've
stopped earlier.

21:40.967 --> 21:44.304
[ Chuckles ]
♪♪ Bobby McGee ♪♪♪♪

21:44.370 --> 21:47.407
‐ [ Di Di Coughing ]
‐ [ Engine Sputtering ]

21:48.909 --> 21:51.011
[ Shouting ]
What the hell's goin' on?

21:51.077 --> 21:54.380
[ Wayne ]
Just‐‐ Just be calm. Keep that
ice bag against your head.

21:54.447 --> 21:57.951
Don't you tell me what to do,
and you keep your dirty hands
away from me.

21:58.018 --> 22:00.521
Shut up, Hugh.
Don't tell me to shut up.
I'll say whatever I‐‐

22:00.587 --> 22:03.690
You shut up.
Car keys.

22:03.757 --> 22:06.126
What?
Give me your car keys
right now.

22:06.192 --> 22:08.394
Oh, hold on. I‐‐

22:09.896 --> 22:12.733
‐ Shit.
‐ You lost your car keys?

22:12.799 --> 22:16.603
Oh, no, no. Shit.
Shit, it's‐‐

22:19.940 --> 22:22.809
No, it's, uh‐‐
You lookin' for this?

22:29.950 --> 22:33.353
‐ Yeah.
‐ Fell out of your coat
while you was unconscious.

22:36.322 --> 22:38.224
Thought I'd keep it
for safekeepin'.

22:38.291 --> 22:40.360
Thanks.

22:40.426 --> 22:42.663
‐ Uh‐‐
‐ Dale.

22:42.729 --> 22:44.998
Dale.

22:46.567 --> 22:48.735
Tussey Custom molded grip.

22:50.270 --> 22:52.205
Matter of fact, it is.

22:52.272 --> 22:54.875
<i>Fact it is. Sweet.</i>

22:54.941 --> 22:57.744
Okay, car keys now.

22:57.811 --> 22:59.613
<i>Quickly!</i>

22:59.680 --> 23:01.081
Ah.

23:02.916 --> 23:07.087
So, Dale,
know your Tussey, huh?
Huh.

23:07.153 --> 23:09.289
Yeah, I know my guns.

23:09.355 --> 23:12.325
I can't find the keys.
I'll move it first thing
in the morning.

23:12.392 --> 23:16.062
Is that your vehicle too?
Yes, that is.

23:16.129 --> 23:19.399
You got a busted
taillight there.
Yes. Fender bender.

23:19.465 --> 23:21.134
[ Imitates Crash ]
With the Denali?

23:21.201 --> 23:23.136
No.

23:24.538 --> 23:27.407
Well, you can't drive around
like that.

23:28.709 --> 23:31.111
I know.
You want some help
with it?

23:32.979 --> 23:35.115
No, I'll be fine.
Well, they probably got
some replacement bulbs...

23:35.181 --> 23:37.851
in the trunk there.
Uh, yes.
I‐I believe they do.

23:37.918 --> 23:40.654
But I'll‐I'll be fine.
[ Chuckles ]
Well, you sure?

23:40.721 --> 23:42.689
Yeah.
It'll only take
a second.

23:42.756 --> 23:45.592
I like to do those things
myself, you know.

23:45.659 --> 23:47.961
Shows you're a man
about the house.

23:48.028 --> 23:50.564
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

23:50.631 --> 23:54.735
What's that?
What was that?

23:54.801 --> 23:58.171
‐ Well, that sound.
‐ Is that an owl?

23:58.238 --> 24:01.374
Sounds like a cell phone.
Oh, that's‐‐
that's my cell phone.

24:01.441 --> 24:03.343
In the trunk?
Yeah.

24:03.409 --> 24:05.512
[ Ringing Continues ]

24:06.513 --> 24:08.348
Well, aren't you
gonna answer it?

24:08.414 --> 24:12.252
No.
Well, it's 5:00 in the morning.
It could be important.

24:12.318 --> 24:15.388
Not at 5:00 in the morning.

24:15.455 --> 24:18.324
My kids,
they did this.

24:18.391 --> 24:20.527
That's where
they hid it. Oh.

24:20.594 --> 24:23.597
Well, okay. It's
none of my business.
I've
been lookin' for it all day.

24:23.664 --> 24:25.732
Well‐‐
The kids, they just‐‐

24:25.799 --> 24:28.334
My eldest, I just
can't deal with him.
He's just does this.

24:28.401 --> 24:31.337
Well, it's none of
my business, sir.
You have a good evening.

24:31.404 --> 24:32.539
Thank you very much,
Officer.

24:32.606 --> 24:33.874
[ Gunshot ]

24:33.940 --> 24:36.543
[ Dog Barking ]
That was a gunshot.

24:36.610 --> 24:38.979
That sounded like
a loud cough.

24:39.045 --> 24:41.748
I have to investigate this,
Mr. Rich.
I don't even have a gun.

24:41.815 --> 24:44.718
I‐‐ I know who it is.
It's my friend,
and he has a cough‐‐

24:44.785 --> 24:47.087
Look, I have to do my job,
Mr. Rich.
No, it's‐‐

24:47.153 --> 24:50.190
Step away from the path, sir.
I can't. I pay your wages
and know my rights.

24:50.256 --> 24:52.893
Step away from
the path now, sir!
I will not do that.

24:52.959 --> 24:55.629
Step away from
the path, sir!
I cannot do that.

24:55.696 --> 24:57.931
[ Gunshot ]
[ Glass Shattering ]

24:57.998 --> 25:00.701
That‐‐

25:00.767 --> 25:03.604
That's what I'm trying
to tell you, Dale.
[ Laughing ]

25:03.670 --> 25:06.406
Tussey's got
a hairline trigger.
Whoo!

25:06.472 --> 25:08.509
Sure does.
♪♪♪♪ [ Rock, Indistinct ]

25:08.575 --> 25:10.677
Who the hell
are you?

25:10.744 --> 25:13.580
Sir, I have
reason to believe
there was a gunshot.

25:13.647 --> 25:15.682
Nope.
There no gunshot.

25:15.749 --> 25:18.752
♪♪ Wrapped up by love
Surrounded by hate ♪♪

25:18.819 --> 25:22.455
Sir, I heard a gunshot.
Now, are you the owner of the‐‐

25:22.523 --> 25:24.958
Who the hell
are you?
Hugh, calm down.

25:25.025 --> 25:28.629
This is Officer Moody.
Officer Delroy Moody.

25:28.695 --> 25:30.697
Security.
He's not even a cop.

25:32.032 --> 25:34.801
Sir, I'm gonna ask you again.
Where is the gun?

25:34.868 --> 25:38.338
Uh‐‐
Shut up. Don't give it
to him, Dale.

25:38.404 --> 25:40.574
<i>[ Delroy ]</i>
<i>I think your friend here</i>
<i>is a little drunk.</i>

25:40.641 --> 25:44.277
<i>He's trespassin'!</i>
<i>You tell him, "Go home."</i>

25:44.344 --> 25:47.848
‐ Shut up, Hugh.
‐ Sir, let's just try
to be responsible here.

25:47.914 --> 25:50.450
<i>[ Hugh ]</i>
<i>He's got no power.</i>
<i>He's a rent‐a‐cop.</i>

25:50.517 --> 25:52.586
He is bullshit!

25:52.653 --> 25:56.823
Now, be a man and tell him
to go home!

25:58.959 --> 26:00.761
Sir, please.

26:00.827 --> 26:04.197
You heard the man.
Go home.

26:07.133 --> 26:09.870
[ Hugh Stammering ]

26:09.936 --> 26:13.006
Jesus, Dale! I didn't say
pull the gun on him.

26:13.073 --> 26:16.042
<i>Dale, give the officer</i>
<i>the gun, please.</i>

26:16.109 --> 26:19.312
I said go home.

26:19.379 --> 26:22.583
Sir, I can't go home.

26:22.649 --> 26:25.018
I am on duty.
This is my job.

26:25.085 --> 26:28.054
If I see alcohol
and there is a gun involved,

26:28.121 --> 26:30.557
I'm required by law
to confiscate the gun.

26:30.624 --> 26:32.859
Well, come and get it.

26:34.127 --> 26:36.296
‐ Dale.
‐ Dale.

26:36.362 --> 26:39.633
No, I said‐‐
I said come and get it,
bullshit man.

26:39.700 --> 26:42.302
♪♪♪♪ [ Continues, Indistinct ]

26:49.342 --> 26:51.778
Put the gun down, Dale.

26:54.414 --> 26:56.783
Make me.

27:03.857 --> 27:05.826
Just how do you want
this to end?

27:05.892 --> 27:09.062
Do you wanna
take him out too?

27:10.496 --> 27:14.367
Do you want to go
to prison, or...

27:16.002 --> 27:18.071
do you want to be
my partner?

27:20.707 --> 27:25.078
Just how much blood
do you want on your hands?

27:28.114 --> 27:30.450
♪♪ Stick your teeth in ♪♪

27:30.517 --> 27:32.285
♪♪ Trust that you weep ♪♪
50‐50.

27:32.352 --> 27:35.689
‐ ♪♪ Snake bite its tail ♪♪
‐ Yeah?

27:35.756 --> 27:38.358
♪♪ Circle complete ♪♪

27:38.424 --> 27:42.796
♪♪ Starvin' yourself
You feed off the pain ♪♪

27:42.863 --> 27:48.134
♪♪ That larger than God
Control of the rain ♪♪

27:48.201 --> 27:50.136
Okay.

27:50.203 --> 27:52.372
Okay.

27:54.508 --> 27:57.143
[ Laughing ]

27:58.478 --> 28:00.380
Whoo!
[ Hugh ]
Jesus.

28:08.488 --> 28:11.925
Blunt, huh?
Don't like the smell
of this town.

28:11.992 --> 28:14.260
All right.
Blunt's what we got.

28:14.327 --> 28:17.497
We're gonna get a car
and get the hell out, right?
Mom, I'm starving.

28:17.564 --> 28:21.968
I could use a shower!
Honey, you got a bug
in your hair, okay?

28:22.035 --> 28:25.606
Come on, girl.
A normal breakfast is
all we're asking for.

28:25.672 --> 28:29.342
[ Cael ] I'd just like to
point out that if you hadn't
got rid of the toolbox,

28:29.409 --> 28:32.378
we wouldn't be in this mess.
I had to take it out
for Sammi's books.

28:32.445 --> 28:34.848
You should've spoke up.
Grandma looks tired.

28:34.915 --> 28:36.883
I think we need to get her
something to eat.

28:36.950 --> 28:39.920
God, when'd you kids
become so soft?

28:39.986 --> 28:42.923
Mama, y'all want
some pancakes?

28:44.457 --> 28:47.694
Mama?
Mama, talk to me.

28:47.761 --> 28:50.496
Is she dead?

28:51.598 --> 28:54.367
Mama? Mama.

28:54.434 --> 28:57.403
Cael, put her over there
on that bench.
Now, honey, be careful.

28:57.470 --> 29:00.974
Mama.
Okay. Here we go.
You're all right.

29:01.041 --> 29:04.611
Mind her head.
Oh, Mama, please don't die.

29:04.678 --> 29:07.180
Is she breathin'?
Mmm.

29:07.247 --> 29:11.685
I can hear her heart.
Di, you hear her heart?
Uh‐‐

29:11.752 --> 29:14.187
Yeah. It's just faint.

29:14.254 --> 29:16.289
We gotta take her
to the hospital.

29:16.356 --> 29:19.059
Hospital.

29:19.125 --> 29:21.194
[ Delroy ]
Mr. Rich, I have to report
this to the police.

29:21.261 --> 29:24.430
A law was broken.
Officer Delroy‐‐
Please call me Doug, okay?

29:24.497 --> 29:27.534
I just want to say one thing.
Do you know who
that man is over there?

29:27.601 --> 29:29.970
Like I said, I'm new here.

29:30.036 --> 29:33.339
Well, he is Hugh Panetta.
I mean, he made all this.

29:33.406 --> 29:36.643
Doug, with all due respect,
God made all this.

29:36.710 --> 29:40.380
No, no, no, no.
All‐‐ All this.
This, the Edenfalls.

29:40.446 --> 29:44.818
Hugh Panetta, his company
carved out and created
this community of Edenfalls.

29:44.885 --> 29:47.320
I mean, you got him
to thank for your job.

29:49.556 --> 29:52.826
Well, I suppose
technically I did trespass
on your property.

29:52.893 --> 29:55.662
Yeah, well, that is‐‐
That's a legal situation
you got yourself in there.

29:55.729 --> 29:59.265
I know. I'm a lawyer.
But I still have to
turn in this gun.

29:59.332 --> 30:01.802
[ Wayne ]
Then you turn the gun in.
You keep it in the bag.

30:01.868 --> 30:04.370
‐ <i>It's safe there.</i>
‐ <i>[ Hugh ]</i>
<i>What the hell? God.</i>

30:04.437 --> 30:08.675
Well, Doug,
for your information,
I am not bullshit.

30:08.742 --> 30:10.911
It is my job to keep
this place safe.

30:10.977 --> 30:13.446
I know.
And I'm gonna do it.

30:13.514 --> 30:16.583
Thank you. Thank you.

30:16.650 --> 30:18.619
Thank you so much.

30:18.685 --> 30:20.687
<i>[ Hugh ]</i>
<i>Oh, hey.</i>

30:20.754 --> 30:23.356
Screw him.
I got another one.

30:23.423 --> 30:25.659
[ Buzzing ]

30:25.726 --> 30:27.994
Okay.
[ Claps Hands ]

30:28.061 --> 30:30.697
We gotta get you back home.
I can't go home.

30:30.764 --> 30:34.234
[ Sighs ]
My heart's broken, Doug.
I lost my wife.

30:34.300 --> 30:36.970
What did you do?
Tried to give her
this ring.

30:37.037 --> 30:39.439
And I was all excited
about it too.

30:39.506 --> 30:42.042
<i>I wrapped it up. I stuck it</i>
<i>under her pillow. Shit.</i>

30:42.108 --> 30:44.044
She didn't like it?
<i>No, she liked it.</i>

30:44.110 --> 30:46.212
[ Groans ]
God.
What's your problem then?

30:46.279 --> 30:49.249
She didn't love it,
what the problem is.

30:49.315 --> 30:51.885
‐ How do you know
she didn't love it?
‐ The eyes. I could tell.

30:51.952 --> 30:56.122
Somethin' in the eyes. You know,
when a girl's lyin' to you,
she's tryin' to be polite.

30:56.189 --> 30:59.860
I said,
"Baby, you don't love it.
Why are you lying to me?"

30:59.926 --> 31:03.764
And she's all,
"Dreams are complicated, Hugh."

31:03.830 --> 31:07.033
Perhaps she was telling
the truth about the ring.
Lyin', Doug.

31:07.100 --> 31:11.237
I know what lying is.
So I asked her politely...

31:11.304 --> 31:14.274
<i>not to lie to me</i>
<i>and to be happy!</i>

31:14.340 --> 31:17.443
I mean, she jiggy‐danced
in Vegas for a living.

31:17.511 --> 31:20.747
Now she's living in a house
on a hill. I'm making
her dreams come true.

31:20.814 --> 31:23.249
Least she could do
is be happy about it.

31:23.316 --> 31:25.986
Huh? Huh?

31:26.052 --> 31:29.656
So she cried a little.
Said she was happy.

31:29.723 --> 31:34.327
And I guess I sorta took
the ring and just stuck it
on her finger.

31:34.394 --> 31:38.098
Ring didn't fit.
It's too small.
I drew some blood.

31:38.164 --> 31:41.067
She called me a monster,
saddest man she ever met.

31:41.134 --> 31:44.270
So I pulled it off
and threw it in the toilet.

31:45.839 --> 31:47.908
‐ I think it broke.
‐ The toilet?

31:49.175 --> 31:53.146
The finger. Anyway,

31:53.213 --> 31:56.249
she was in pretty bad pain,
and I tried to call 911.

31:56.316 --> 31:59.119
‐ She kicks me out
on the street.
‐ How'd you get the ring back?

31:59.185 --> 32:01.421
‐ What?
‐ From the toilet?

32:03.524 --> 32:07.360
What's she mean,
"Dreams are complicated,"
Doug?

32:07.427 --> 32:09.596
Oh, God, I don't know.
Maybe she meant, you know,

32:09.663 --> 32:12.966
now that she's got the house
on the hill, she doesn't want
the house on the hill.

32:13.033 --> 32:15.368
Then why'd she marry me?
Maybe she married you
for who you are.

32:15.435 --> 32:18.271
Who I am is a guy
with a house on the hill!

32:18.338 --> 32:21.041
Look, you busted her finger.

32:21.107 --> 32:24.678
You want to apologize,
you get down on your hands
and knees. You crawl...

32:24.745 --> 32:26.547
and you ask
for forgiveness.

32:26.613 --> 32:29.449
Then you get some time off
and you take a vacation.

32:29.516 --> 32:31.952
Mmm. No.
No. Can't.

32:32.018 --> 32:34.087
You can't crawl on
your hands and knees?

32:34.154 --> 32:36.990
No. Can't take a vacation
right now.
Hugh,

32:37.057 --> 32:38.825
just take a vacation, okay?
[ Groans ]
Can't.

32:38.892 --> 32:41.628
Take a vacation.
I can't. Come here, buddy.
Come here.

32:41.695 --> 32:43.597
Take a look at this.

32:44.931 --> 32:48.702
Bayou Hills, Doug.
We can't pass it up.

32:48.769 --> 32:51.204
Hugh, there will always
be another deal.
No.

32:52.438 --> 32:55.108
Not gonna be another Bayou Hills
as long as we live.

32:55.175 --> 32:57.277
That's why I came over here
to talk to you tonight.

32:57.343 --> 32:59.479
No, you came over here to talk
to me about your wife.

32:59.546 --> 33:03.684
Her too. Here.
Look at this.
Christ.

33:04.918 --> 33:07.487
Uh, right. Sweet.
Excellent.

33:07.554 --> 33:11.157
Sweet? It's the deal
of a lifetime, Doug.

33:11.224 --> 33:13.660
The state took our bid.
We're all in.

33:13.727 --> 33:17.463
We're not callin',
we're not raisin'‐‐
We're all in.

33:17.531 --> 33:19.633
[ Laughs ]
Five days to raise the money.

33:19.700 --> 33:23.136
This goes through,
Panco makes 150 million.

33:23.203 --> 33:27.541
I make a third of that, and you
cash in on a baker's dozen‐‐
13 million, Doug.

33:28.975 --> 33:31.277
Thirteen million?

33:43.389 --> 33:47.861
Well, um, your mother's
heartbeat is very faint.

33:47.928 --> 33:52.298
Well, what's wrong with her?
Calm down, ma'am.
She, uh, has arrhythmia.

33:52.365 --> 33:54.300
Now, that's either
from heart disease,

33:54.367 --> 33:57.638
or she's dehydrated
and drunk.

33:58.404 --> 34:00.373
<i>Has she been drinking?</i>

34:00.440 --> 34:03.176
No. Of course not.
You're sure of this?

34:03.243 --> 34:06.479
‐ Not that I know of.
‐ 'Cause she reeks of alcohol.

34:07.581 --> 34:09.750
[ Sniffs ]

34:15.789 --> 34:18.158
♪♪♪♪ [ Radio: Country ]

34:20.594 --> 34:24.464
Mmm. No go?
Can I see your I. D.,
please?

34:24.531 --> 34:28.168
Yeah. Hold on.

34:28.234 --> 34:31.538
Well, there we are.
[ Chuckles ]
[ Sighs ]

34:31.605 --> 34:33.739
Can you hear me,
sweetheart? Uh‐‐

34:33.806 --> 34:35.542
Morgenstern.
Morgenstern?

34:35.609 --> 34:39.813
Ms. Morgenstern, uh,
would you try to sit up for me.

34:39.880 --> 34:43.049
‐ It's Dr. Morgenstern.
‐ Oh, is she a doctor?

34:43.116 --> 34:47.087
‐ No.
‐ Uh, I want a large Cadillac.

34:47.152 --> 34:50.591
[ Laughs ]
Everyone does, dear.

34:50.657 --> 34:53.458
Does she have dementia?
We think.

34:53.527 --> 34:55.360
‐ You think?
‐ Uh, we're sure.

34:55.428 --> 34:57.263
‐ Well, how was she diagnosed?
‐ Alzheimer's.

34:57.330 --> 35:00.166
‐ Dementia.
‐ Well, they're‐‐

35:00.233 --> 35:03.369
You know, there was
a big debate goin' on among
the doctors who treated her.

35:06.339 --> 35:09.543
So many things in here.

35:11.177 --> 35:13.346
There we go. Yeah.

35:14.681 --> 35:16.717
Thank you,
Miss Prestwich.
Of course.

35:16.783 --> 35:20.621
Just never know who's spending
your money these days.
Don't I know it.

35:20.687 --> 35:23.289
How old is your mother,
Mrs. Prestwich?
She's 78.

35:23.356 --> 35:28.629
Seventy‐eight?
Um, let me see here.

35:28.695 --> 35:33.433
Yes, uh‐‐ Your daughter
says she's 91.

35:33.499 --> 35:37.337
‐ Well, that's incorrect.
‐ All right then.

35:37.403 --> 35:40.106
I'm gonna need
to admit your mother
to Blunt Presbyterian.

35:40.173 --> 35:44.277
What? She's just drunk.
Ma'am, you don't know much
about your mother's health.

35:44.344 --> 35:47.681
You gave her alcohol.
You barely know how old she is.

35:47.748 --> 35:51.284
<i>Now, if anything,</i>
<i>that's elder abuse.</i>

35:51.351 --> 35:53.620
You sayin' I abuse
my mother?

35:53.687 --> 35:56.389
‐ Do you know how old
your mother is?
‐ I beg your pardon.

35:56.456 --> 35:59.793
Do you know how old your mother
or wife is? Do you know about
their health affairs?

35:59.860 --> 36:02.729
When was the last time
your wife had a Pap smear?

36:02.796 --> 36:05.131
‐ [ Chuckles ]
Well, as a matter of fact‐‐
‐ I don't wanna know that.

36:05.198 --> 36:08.735
<i>That's not the point.</i>
<i>I love her.</i>

36:08.802 --> 36:11.772
How dare you accuse me of
elder abuse? I'm outraged!

36:11.838 --> 36:15.175
You just calm down, ma'am.
Your mother is coming with me,

36:15.241 --> 36:17.678
and she's coming to
Blunt Presbyterian.

36:17.744 --> 36:22.248
<i>Now, you just</i>
<i>wait here a moment,</i>
<i>and I'll be right back.</i>

36:23.249 --> 36:25.251
Son of a bitch.

36:25.318 --> 36:29.322
White coat say I don't love
my mama and take care of her.
I'm a good daughter.

36:29.389 --> 36:31.592
Have you‐‐ Have you used
that card recently?

36:31.658 --> 36:35.228
Um, you know, I don't know.
May‐Maybe not recently.

36:35.295 --> 36:40.133
Yeah. That must be
the problem then. Bet they
froze it for security.

36:40.200 --> 36:42.268
Ma'am, please.

36:42.335 --> 36:44.838
I really just want to get
my grandmother treated.

36:44.905 --> 36:47.641
That's why you should give
those Visa folks a call.

36:51.678 --> 36:54.347
‐ The card's dead.
‐ Oh, shit. Shit.

36:54.414 --> 36:56.950
If they froze Prestwich,
they froze 'em all, huh?
I guess. Probably.

36:57.017 --> 37:00.621
‐ Hey, you got any cards?
‐ Uh, I‐I‐I left 'em.

37:00.687 --> 37:03.323
I left all my credit cards
and cash.

37:03.389 --> 37:05.526
‐ You ran away
without a penny?
‐ Yeah.

37:05.592 --> 37:08.494
‐ Why?
‐ I‐‐ I thought
it'd be more fun.

37:08.562 --> 37:11.497
You know, kinda
live off the earth.

37:13.099 --> 37:15.201
Okay, you gotta get cash.

37:15.268 --> 37:17.103
Okay. All right.
Pay with that.

37:17.170 --> 37:19.973
Find out exactly
what medications
they need for her.

37:20.040 --> 37:21.975
Okay.

37:23.544 --> 37:26.479
Screw Blunt Presbyterian.

37:26.547 --> 37:28.749
She just gotta
get rehydrated.

37:28.815 --> 37:32.519
<i>Okay. Y'all wanna</i>
<i>live off the earth?</i>
<i>Now's your chance.</i>

37:33.687 --> 37:36.590
[ Scrubbing ]

38:08.555 --> 38:10.490
I can't believe
Grandma was drunk.
She was.

38:10.557 --> 38:12.492
Whew!
She wouldn't even
let me have a sip.

38:12.559 --> 38:15.495
Wow. She drank that
whole thing of whiskey.

38:15.562 --> 38:17.831
I know.
That was‐‐ That's,
like, unbelievable.

38:17.898 --> 38:19.733
[ Cael ]
Hey.

38:19.800 --> 38:21.768
‐ What's goin' on here?
‐ Football night.

38:21.835 --> 38:23.670
Oh, that figures.
<i>[ Woman ] Everything</i>
<i>all right here, folks?</i>

38:23.737 --> 38:26.206
Great. Thank you.
Good. Thank you.

38:26.272 --> 38:29.342
‐ You ordered too much.
‐ So what? We'll just take
some of it with us.

38:29.409 --> 38:32.613
We don't have the cash, Di Di.
We had to pay for Mama.
We're goin' on the road.

38:32.679 --> 38:34.781
We gotta pay for gas
and drugs for her.

38:34.848 --> 38:37.483
‐ Whatever you haven't started,
we're sending back.
‐ I'm eatin' my steak and eggs.

38:37.551 --> 38:38.719
‐ Cael.
‐ Ma?

38:38.785 --> 38:41.487
Cael.
Ma. I'm gonna get up.

38:41.555 --> 38:43.089
Don't you do any‐‐
I'm gettin' up.

38:43.156 --> 38:46.059
Don't you do‐‐
I'm warnin' you.
I'm goin' to the bathroom.

38:46.126 --> 38:48.862
Such a little bastard.

39:04.344 --> 39:07.047
Can I eat my steak and eggs?

39:12.118 --> 39:15.556
‐ Cael.
‐ That's nice.
That's real nice.

39:15.622 --> 39:18.925
<i>You robbin' old ladies now?</i>
<i>Hmm? Feel good?</i>

39:18.992 --> 39:21.628
Do you feel good? That was
a shitty thing to do.

39:21.695 --> 39:24.531
And let that be
your "come‐upponce."

39:24.598 --> 39:26.933
Mom, I think the word
is "comeuppance."

39:27.000 --> 39:29.803
What are you,
the word police?
You shut your piehole.

39:29.870 --> 39:32.639
Wrap that steak in a napkin.
Go steal me a car.

39:35.542 --> 39:37.811
Don't you look at me
like that.
Can I come?

39:37.878 --> 39:41.381
No, sweetheart.
Starsky don't need no Hutch.

39:48.288 --> 39:50.691
You all right there,
ma'am?
Uh‐‐

39:50.757 --> 39:54.528
‐ Are you short?
‐ I thought I had $40.

39:54.595 --> 39:57.297
Oh, sweetheart.
I know how that is.
Here you go.

39:57.363 --> 39:59.465
Don't you mind that.

40:11.845 --> 40:14.247
Ow. Jesus!

40:14.314 --> 40:17.383
Nina. Scared me to death.

40:17.450 --> 40:20.053
I just want to see
how it's done.

40:23.289 --> 40:27.027
[ Engine Cranks, Starts ]

40:30.030 --> 40:32.498
Which way, Doug?

40:34.367 --> 40:36.703
Which way to
the light?
[ Sighs ]

40:36.770 --> 40:39.072
[ Wayne ]
Just through these doors.

40:39.139 --> 40:43.610
[ Door Opens ]
[ Cell Phone Buzzing ]

40:44.545 --> 40:46.513
[ Door Closes ]
[ Beeps ]

40:46.580 --> 40:49.783
I can't talk.
I'm with him now.

40:49.850 --> 40:51.952
Hey.

40:52.018 --> 40:54.020
This goddamn town is
giving me the creeps.

40:54.087 --> 40:57.290
Let's get Mama
and get outta here.
[ Cell Phone Beeping ]

40:57.357 --> 41:00.426
‐ Wayne?
‐ Hey, partner!

41:00.493 --> 41:02.596
We said 50‐50.

41:02.663 --> 41:05.398
‐ Wayne?
‐ [ Whispers ]
I love you.

41:05.465 --> 41:09.002
‐ Huh?
‐ I love you.

41:09.069 --> 41:12.639
Well, okay. I love you.
Where are you?

41:12.706 --> 41:15.308
‐ Uh, I'm at the house.
‐ Where's Pete?

41:15.375 --> 41:17.243
We are in this together.

41:17.310 --> 41:20.747
Did you really think
that spikin' my scotch
would lick me?

41:21.815 --> 41:23.750
Pete's fine.
Everything's all right.

41:23.817 --> 41:27.053
Everything's all right.
Wayne?

41:27.120 --> 41:30.390
‐ Well, everything's all right.
‐ So where do you think
you're goin'?

41:30.456 --> 41:33.359
Oh, Jesus. Oh, Jesus.
Oh, Jesus.

41:33.426 --> 41:36.563
This is my van.

41:37.564 --> 41:40.200
Hey, hey, the gang's
all here.

41:42.068 --> 41:44.370
Get out of the car.

41:44.437 --> 41:47.373
I am talking about
a certain dead body
festering in the trunk.

41:47.440 --> 41:49.976
I know what
you're talking about,
and I am dealing with it.

41:50.043 --> 41:53.213
So why don't you get out
of the goddamn car now?

41:53.279 --> 41:57.751
This ain't your car.
And that ain't your house.

41:57.818 --> 42:01.922
And I don't know Doug Rich,
but I'm assuming he, too,
is in a festering condition.

42:01.988 --> 42:04.658
Am I right? So,

42:04.725 --> 42:10.363
you rat me out, I rat you out,
vice versa and so on.

42:10.430 --> 42:13.734
Mutually insured
destruction.

42:13.800 --> 42:16.670
We're in this together.
Two peas in a pod.

42:16.737 --> 42:20.440
Mutually assured destruction,
you asshole.

42:20.507 --> 42:26.412
That's right. Mutually assured,
mutually insured
to the bitter end.

42:26.479 --> 42:31.284
So, Douglas,
what's the plan?

42:32.352 --> 42:34.254
[ Sighs ]
